  "prompt": "From which institute should I learn post production and lightning, sound camera etc for my YouTube channel in Delhi?",
  "response": "Delhi offers several reputable institutes where you can learn post-production, lighting, sound, and camera techniques, which are crucial for creating quality content for your YouTube channel. Here are some notable options:\n\n1. **Film and Television Institute of India (FTII) - Delhi Campus**: While based in Pune, FTII occasionally offers short courses and workshops in Delhi that cover various aspects of filmmaking, including post-production and technical skills.\n\n2. **AAFT - Asian Academy of Film and Television**: Located in Noida, AAFT offers comprehensive courses in film and television production, including specialization in post-production, lighting, and sound design.\n\n3. **MATRIM - Maulana Azad Institute of Humanities, Technology & Management**: Offers courses in media studies that include practical skill development in sound, camera, and lighting.\n\n4. **Delhi College of Photography**: Known for photography, but also offers workshops and courses in video production techniques that cover camera and lighting.\n\n5. **The Delhi School of Communication (DSC)**: Offers various media and communication courses, including video production techniques.\n\n6. **Jamia Millia Islamia**: Their AJK Mass Communication Research Centre provides short-term courses and degree programs in media and communication, including film production skills.\n\n7. **FTI - Film and Television Institute of India (Regional Chapter)**: Sometimes offers curated workshops in Delhi on various technical and creative aspects of filmmaking.\n\nWhen choosing an institute, consider factors like curriculum, faculty expertise, duration of the course, and hands-on training opportunities. It's also beneficial to look at reviews and possibly reach out to alumni for their insights.",
